div.div:

“Ice placed within a shop or room


Will turn to water, we presume;


For, 'tis a solvent, all agree;


But here IN-solvent ice we see.


“Yet, though we cannot solve the ice,


We solve the riddle in a trice;


It comes from Pennsylvania's State,


And therefore will not liquidate."

div.p:
The essays in this little volume are already well known to the readers of the New York Turf Register, and other sporting magazines;
               and the popularity of the author’s name will doubtless give them a
               wide circulation among readers in general.
